The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 21 March is 41,120 (4,759.4 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 16 March, there were 309 new confirmed cases (35.8 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 09 March, there were 284 new cases and so the new cases have risen by 9% (25 extra cases).
